abstract: Public charter schools, long protected as a bipartisan way to expand school choice, are suddenly in a political battle as both parties shift to other priorities.
snippet: Public charter schools, long protected as a bipartisan way to expand school choice, are suddenly in a political battle as both parties shift to other priorities.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Public charter schools — caught between growing Democratic disenchantment and a Trump administration shift toward private schools — are preparing for political battle, as the long-protected education sector finds itself on the verge of abandonment.

abstract: The disease is poised to target globalism’s weak points and to exploit American misgovernment and mistrust.
snippet: The disease is poised to target globalism’s weak points and to exploit American misgovernment and mistrust.
lead_paragraph: A truism of our times is that media hysteria quickly envelops every major story, with social media virality and cable-news imperatives combining to make any domestic controversy feel like Watergate, if not Fort Sumter, and any international incident feel like the assassination of Franz Ferdinand — until the next story rolls around and last week’s crisis is forgotten.

headline_main: The Coronavirus Is More Than a Disease. It’s a Test.

abstract: There are people willing to listen to women now, and sometimes what we say has consequences.
snippet: There are people willing to listen to women now, and sometimes what we say has consequences.
lead_paragraph: When I was young I had no words. I read voraciously, I loved books, stories, language. I was trying to become a writer, and so I lived for words and by words. I poured out my thoughts and some of the hopes and fears that were beginning to take shape in long conversations with friends. But words failed me when I needed them most.

abstract: You can promise voters something our narrow-minded president won’t.
snippet: You can promise voters something our narrow-minded president won’t.
lead_paragraph: If this election turns out to be just between a self-proclaimed socialist and an undiagnosed sociopath, we will be in a terrible, terrible place as a country. How do we prevent that?

abstract: A U.S. judge barred the government from relocating coronavirus patients to southern California for another week on Monday and ordered it to discuss the move with state officials.

lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - A U.S. judge barred the government from relocating coronavirus patients to southern California for another week on Monday and ordered it to discuss the move with state officials.

abstract: As President Trump toured India’s capital, at least 11 people were killed in mob violence that upended a working-class neighborhood.
snippet: As President Trump toured India’s capital, at least 11 people were killed in mob violence that upended a working-class neighborhood.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — A mob of Hindu men, their foreheads marked by a saffron stripe, angrily patrolled the streets carrying iron bars, clubs and a bright blue aluminum baseball bat. They were itching for a fight.
